This paper is about speech recognition using neural network models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with NLP and machine learning. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and model architecture, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms and multi-head attention could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
